Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Chop the @sweet potato{1} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel!).

Pop the potatoes on a low sided wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, then season with 
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out in a single layer.

Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{18-20%mins}. Turn halfway 
through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @chicken breast{260%g}(diced), season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and 
stir-fry until browned, ~{3-4%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken cooks, halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and 
thinly sliced).

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(grated) (or use a garlic press).

Thinly slice half the @red chilli{1/2}(thinly sliced) and finely chop the rest.

Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}(zested and halved).

Once the chicken is browned, add the shallot to the pan and fry together with the chicken 
until starting to soften, ~{3-4%mins}.

Stir in the garlic, @ginger puree{1}(ginger puree), finely chopped chilli (careful it's hot! 
Add less if you don't like heat) and @tomato puree{30%g}. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @water{200%ml} and @chicken stock powder{1}.

Bring to the boil and simmer until the sauce has reduced slightly and the flavours have 
developed, ~{3-4%mins}.

Then stir in the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time until it's wilted and everything 
is piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Remove from the heat, squeeze in some of the lime juice and add half the @soy sauce{25%ml}.

Taste and add more lime juice and soy sauce if you feel it needs it.

Stir in the roasted sweet potato.

Serve in #bowls{} with the sliced chilli (Careful it's hot! Add less if you don't like heat) 
and lime zest sprinkled on top. Enjoy!

> MOD Step 2: If you've chosen to receive diced chicken breast instead of diced chicken 
> thigh, just cook it the same way the recipe tells you to cook the diced thigh in the 
> step above and in the rest of the recipe.